<sections title="EclipseLink 2.5.0 Release">

	<section class="title">
		<description>
			<h1>EclipseLink 2.5.0</h1>
			<p> The primary focus of the EclipseLink 2.5 release is the delivery
				of the JPA 2.1 (JSR 338) Reference Implementation.
			</p>
			<p>
				New features include:
				<ul>
					<li>Full JPA 2.1 support</li>
					<li>New DB platforms: Hanna and Pervasive</li>
					<li>JPA-RS Enhancements</li>
					<li>MOXy - NamedObjectGraphs</li>
				</ul>
			</p>
		</description>
	</section>

	<section class="main" name="New and Noteworthy" image="/sequoyah/images/CC_news.png">

		<description>
			<table>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>JPA 2.1 - Criteria Bulk Update/Delete</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						The Criteria framework is an API for creating
						typesafe and/or dynamic Java Persistence queries that was added in
						JPA 2.0. Similar in style to the EclipseLink Query and Expression
						framework. Until JPA 2.1, using Critera to perform deletes or
						updates was not available using the Criteria API. Through the
						addition of CriteriaUpdate/CriteriaDelete classes support for bulk
						update/delete queries has now been added.
					</td>
					<td width="150">
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a
								href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Release/2.5/JPA21/BulkUpdate">Documentation</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>JPA 2.1 - Stored Procedures</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">JPA specification 2.1 has introduced support for
						executing Stored Procedure calls. This includes a new
						StoredProcedureQuery API and Named Stored Procedure Queries
						(pre-existing portions of code on the database).
					</td>
					<td>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a
								href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Release/2.5/JPA21/StoredProcedure">Documentation</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>

				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>JPA 2.1 - JPQL Generic function support</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						The SQL spec and many databases have SQL functions
						that are not covered by the JPA specification. With the latest JPA
						specification the ability to call generic SQL functions was added
						to the JPQL syntax.
					</td>
					<td>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a
								href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Release/2.5/JPA21/JPQLFunction">Documentation</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>

				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>JPA 2.1 - Injectable Entity Listeners</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						Contexts and Dependency Injection (CDI) allows for
						container managed injection of artifacts into Java Objects. This
						feature provides the functionality needed for EclipseLink to
						integrate with CDI to provide for CDI injecting into the Entity
						Listener.
					</td>
					<td>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a
								href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Release/2.5/JPA21/CDIEntityListener">Documentation</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>JPA 2.1 - Treat</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						Allows relationship joins to be treated as a subclass
						of the join type.
					</td>
					<td>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Release/2.5/JPA21/Treat">Documentation</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>JPA 2.1 - Converters</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						Provides control over the conversion from an
						attribute type and value to the corresponding database type and
						value
					</td>
					<td>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a
								href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Release/2.5/JPA21/Converter">Documentation</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>JPA 2.1 - DDL Gen</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						In previous versions for JPA, although DDL generation
						was present it was not standardized or required. JPA 2.1 has added
						standardized provider DDL generation and made DDL generation a
						requirement.
					</td>
					<td>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Release/2.5/JPA21/DDLGen">Documentation</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<h4>JPA 2.1 - Entity Graphs</h4>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr
					style="padding:0.5em;margin:0.5em 0.5em 1em 1em;border:1px solid #D9D9D9;background:#EFEFEF;-moz-border-radius:4px;">
					<td valign="top">
						Entity graphs are subgraphs of the entity model
						metadata. The entity graph contains metamodel representations of a
						set of the entity classes' attributes and metamodel
						representations of related entity classes. A constructed entity
						graph can be used as a template for applying operations like
						attribute loading.
					</td>
					<td>
						<div>
							<img src="/eclipselink/images/doc_small.png" />
							<a
								href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/EclipseLink/Release/2.5/JPA21/EntityGraph">Documentation</a>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>

